!! This structure was made before lifecycle scope was added to config files !!

Reproduction of ATAG Waypoint scenarios in AeroMAPS

The scenarios from the 3rd edition are made based on the 2nd edition, with some adjustments on assumptions regarding:
- Technology: old T5 scenario with focus on hydrogen is removed
- SAF: the mandate quantities are revised downwards, but a steeper ramp-up is assumed (to match their backcasting to
reach 90% SAF in 2050). The split among pathways is also revised, with more emphasis on advanced feedstocks and less on
 HEFA.

SAF quantities were estimated from figures in the report, without the need for extra assumptions of how to split among
feedstocks. Prices however are not disclosed in the document, so they are assumed to be the same as the 2nd edition.

!! ISSUES:
- Demand growth with CAGR do not account for faster growth in early years (both in the 2nd and 3rd edition)
- SAF quantities are explicitly stated in the report, but our estimations of total fuel demand is lower than report
(may be linked to lower demand in early years). Such that, fossil kerosene is phased out in both 2nd and 3rd edition!
